TITLE: Basic Mock Implementation with .mock().using()
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates how to set up a mock implementation for a Database service using Automock's .mock().using() method chain. This approach defines mock behavior during TestBed setup rather than in individual test cases.
SOURCE: https://github.com/suites-dev/suites/blob/master/docs/automock/overview/examples.md#2025-04-21_snippet_4

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
beforeAll(() => {
  const mockUsers: User[] = [{ id: 1, name: 'John' }, { id: 2, name: 'Jane' }];

  const { unit, unitRef } = TestBed.create(UserService)
    .mock(Database)
    .using({ getUsers: async () => mockUsers })
    .compile();

  userService = unit;
  database = unitRef.get(Database);
});
```

