TITLE: Defining Database and UserService Classes in TypeScript
DESCRIPTION: Example code showing the structure of Database and UserService classes, where UserService depends on Database. The Database class has a method to retrieve users, and UserService uses this dependency to implement getAllUsers method.
SOURCE: https://github.com/suites-dev/suites/blob/master/README.md#2025-04-21_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
export class Database {
  async getUsers(): Promise<User[]> { ... }
}

export class UserService {
  constructor(private database: Database) {}

  async getAllUsers(): Promise<User[]> {
    return this.database.getUsers();
  }
}
```

